A Poem Written by an African Shakespeare

Dear white fella
Couple things you should know
When I born, I black
When I grow up, I black
When I go in sun, I black
When I cold, I black
When I scared, I black
When I sick, I black
And when I die, I still black.

You white fella
When you born, you pink
When you grow up, you white
When you go in sun, you red
When you cold, you blue
When you scared, you yellow
When you sick, you green
And when you die, you grey.
And you have the cheek to call me colored?????

I hate when people just drop you from their lives without any explanation or reason at all whatsoever, and the only form of interaction is reading their lj posts, that and when people move away without saying goodbye, school is a bitch.  Tired as shit, but i have an obligation to answer the Call Of Duty (4).

As i drove today, i came to a rapid realization that time is going very fast for me, and i don't really know how to feel about it, nor how to approach it.  On one side i am glad time is speeding by because I am on the verge of graduating and transferring to the U which means I am almost 100% done with school and I cant wait for that but at the same time i feel like i should be moving slower and enjoying things.  Then i realized that i have no one or nothing to slow down for.  I had something at one time, but that thing, or rather person has become little more than a casual acquaintance.  Sometimes it hits me how much i miss her and it really upsets me.  I am not sure if its the events that happened that upset me, or the fact that i let it get me so upset...but when it comes right down to it i would give anything for it to go back the the way it was in the beginning.  When i could truly say i was happy.  I have never felt like that and i feel like it should not have ended like it should.  There are still details i want and need to know but i have abandoned the idea of discussing it any more than I already have.  Time keeps flying and i find myself wondering if I will ever find a reason to slow down.

September 11 

What Russian leader was not allowed to enter Disneyland when he visited America in 1959? 

It was Nikita Khrushev, who was dictator of Russia from 1953 to 1964. Khrushev's announced goal was to spread Communism throughout the world. He was described by journalists as shrewd, earthy, talkative and very energetic. He died on this day in 1971. 

WE WILL NEVER FORGET HOW WE DIDNT LET KHRUSHEV IN!

WOW...that is the only word that encompasses this experience.  This was by far the best movie viewing experience i have ever had the pleasure of being a part of.  I was the third person to show up and waited for over 3 hours to see this movie.  The line alone was amazing, there was laughter throughout the wait.  We frequently chanted "SNAKES ON A PLANE" everytime someone asked what we were seeing, or whenever we felt the need to be loud.  This one woman, feeling the need to be a bitch, walked by us and muttered "its just a movie guys."  She said that too close to the wrong person.  I was not having that kind of disrespect.  So when she walked back by, we all chanted loud and clear for all to hear...PWNED BITCH!  When we finally got in the theatre, someone had a cardboard cutout of Samuel L. Jackson and it was fantastic.  We used a plastic water jug as a beachball, and yelled a whores and bitches in the front row because they were drunk and being idiots.  Lucas came up with an amazing cheer "What do we want?" "SNAKES" "Where do we want them?" "ON A PLANE" "Who do we love?" "SAMUEL L JACKSON" "When do we want it?" "NOW!"  when the movie started, the projector guy was fucking up big time, after all of the previews, and constantly shouting profanities in his general direction, He stopped the movie, fixed the problem, and we got to see more previews, including the TENACIOUS D movie! awesome...The movie was waaaaay better than i expected, words cannot describe how miraculous and divine this movie truly was...I am not going to see this movie again because it will not be the same at all, i never want to ruin this experience...goodnight everyone, watch out for snakes on planes...In the words of Samuel L Jackson..."I AM SICK AND TIRED OF THESE MOTHAFUCKIN SNAKES ON THIS MUTHAFUCKIN PLANE!"
